race.comment: METAL MAN (3) is a talented gelding who was well supported last time in the G3 Vo Rogue Plate at Eagle Farm, but pulled up with an issue.  He'd resumed further improved in an Open 3 at the Gold Coast and fitter he can win drawn handy and with Maloney aboard. TIME OF MY LIFE (9) has had two outings for Gollan and led beaten a whisker at the Sunshine Coast last time. Has more to give and Jones sticks and can use the inside barrier. CHIBA (2) resumes gelded and was last seen winning a Newcastle Maiden from the front heavily bet. She trialled well for the new stable with race rider Rodd in the saddle. Maps for a soft run. TILL DUSK (8) has switched from a Victorian yard and the lightly raced mare also deserves a betting watch. Was last seen winning a Sale Maiden on a heavy track.
